lopment SSL Certificate"}]},{"text":" to for development builds.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Follow the instructions from the SSL certificate assistant."}]}]}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You must update your provisioning profile for the app after you create your SSL certificates. A simple “Refresh” in the organizer will accomplish this.","type":"text"}]}]},{"text":"Step 2: Export Certificate","anchor":"Step-2-Export-Certificate","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Download the production push certificate that you just created and open it with the Keychain Access application."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Keychain Access, click on My Certificates and locate your push certificate."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Export it as a "},{"code":".p12","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" file and use a temporary, unsecure password (you will need this password when uploading your certificate to Braze)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Navigate to the ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitle":"Settings","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/dashboard-01.braze.com\/app_settings\/app_settings","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Settings","type":"text"}],"type":"reference"},{"text":" page in the dashboard and upload your production certificate. ","type":"text"},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-upload.png"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can upload either your development or production push certificates to the dashboard for your distribution provisioning profile apps, but you can only have 